OL,3,CD-Day veteran calls for sacrifice of
OL,4,Clife to be recognised by future
OL,5,Cgenerations
OL,7,FOne of the last surviving D-Day
OL,8,Fveterans has said the thousands of
OL,9,Flives lost in the Normandy landings
OL,10,Fduring the fight against the Nazis
OL,11,Fmust never be forgotten.
OL,13,FAlbert Lamond, 98, will mark the 80th
OL,14,Fanniversary of the Allied landings,
OL,15,Fwhich involved the Navy and RAF, in an
OL,16,Fevent at the Veterans Village in
OL,17,FBishopton, Renfrewshire, run by the
OL,18,FErskine Veterans Charity.
