OL,3,CD-Day veteran calls for sacrifice of
OL,4,Clife to be recognised by future
OL,5,Cgenerations
OL,7,F"The memory of all of those that
OL,8,Fserved must be preserved, our stories
OL,9,Fmust be shared when we are gone, and
OL,10,Fas a country we must educate to ensure
OL,11,Fthat the world never sees a repeat of
OL,12,Fthe events of World War II and D-Day.
OL,14,F"It's our duty to keep the past alive,
OL,15,Fso history does not repeat its darkest
OL,16,Fdays."
