OL,3,CD-Day veteran calls for sacrifice of
OL,4,Clife to be recognised by future
OL,5,Cgenerations
OL,7,FThe crew were constantly watching for
OL,8,FU-boats looking to torpedo the warship
OL,9,Fand had been told they would sacrifice
OL,10,Ftheir own lives if a torpedo was aimed
OL,11,Fat the battleship.
OL,13,FAs a signalman, Mr Lamond was on the
OL,14,Flookout from the bridge throughout the
OL,15,Fbattle, with no cover to defend him `
OL,16,Fand he said he has never forgotten the
OL,17,Fyoung men who died.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/10
