OL,3,CD-Day veteran calls for sacrifice of
OL,4,Clife to be recognised by future
OL,5,Cgenerations
OL,7,F"Our captain says, 'If we see a
OL,8,Ftorpedo going to hit the battleship
OL,9,Fthe Warspite, we'll nip in and take
OL,10,Fthe torpedo'. We were simply there to
OL,11,Fdefend others.
OL,13,F"The importance of the mission wasn't
OL,14,Flost on us ` we knew what we were
OL,15,Fgetting ourselves into.
OL,17,F"It was horrible. It lives with you
OL,18,Fforever. It has never gotten easier.
OL,19,FThere were hundreds of men going
OL,20,Fashore, I can still see them.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUyD@AOU
